# Purpose: Keep generated artifacts, secrets and local tooling noise out of version control.
# Input/Output: Used by Git during status/add operations.
# Invariants: Runtime results and virtual environments are never committed by default.
# Debugging: If an expected file is ignored, run `git check-ignore -v <path>` in a git-enabled clone.

__pycache__/
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.venv/
venv/
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/
.DS_Store
.env
results/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
htmlcov/
